## Interpretation
  - Unidirectional peer copy saturates at 28.6 GB/s ~= 91% of Gen5 x8 theoretical.
  - Bidirectional aggregate 50.0 GB/s (~87% of 2x unidirectional; minor root-complex contention).
  - Peer is 3.1x faster than the host-staged fallback (9.2 GB/s) — this is the gain the
    repo's working routes leave on the table when they detour through host RAM.
